'''Jizz-wail''' was a [[Music/Legends|music]] genre. A [[Unidentified quartet|quartet]] performed some jizz-wail in a crowded square in the [[Eusebus|capital]] of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Euceron]] during the [[Galactic Games/Legends|Galactic Games]]<ref name="TDG" /> of [[27 BBY/Legends|27 BBY]].<ref name="TERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates the events of ''[[Jedi Quest: The Dangerous Games]]'' to [[27 BBY/Legends|27 BBY]].</ref> During the [[Imperial Era/Legends|Imperial Era]], the [[Spacer/Legends|spacer]] [[Gideon (spacer)|Gideon]] heard jizz-wailing in an establishment on<ref name="SS">{{JournalCite|12|Shape-shifters}}</ref> the planet<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|I|115|Centares}}</ref> [[Centares/Legends|Centares]], played on a [[Nalargon/Legends|red ball jett organ]].<ref name="SS" />

==Behind the scenes==
Jizz-wail was first mentioned in the [[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game|roleplaying game]] source article "[[Shape-shifters]]," written by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] for the [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 12|twelfth issue]] of [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]'' magazine and published in [[February]] [[1997]].<ref name="SS" />

